task.summary: Trying a new approach to the SAT-solver, one that is separate from the Hitori. The solver takes a String representation of a CNF-formula as input, dividing it into clauses and variables. To be implemented is Unit Propagation, and a solving mechanism that utilizes this. Additionally, we need a way to convert Variable assignments to a HitoriToCNF object, so that we can check whether it upholds the third rule (all white spaces being connected).
Seemingly functional SAT-solver. Problems with the recursive calls. Must check out.
